		<label>ZhuangZi scarf</label>
		<description>The Zhuangzi scarf is a type of Taoist headwear. Its lower part is square, while the top forms a triangular, roof-like shape. A piece of white jade is set at the front of the cap, symbolizing upright conduct and moral integrity.</description>
